===Verb===
{{en-verb|hold<,,held> off}}

# {{lb|en|idiomatic|transitive}} To delay someone or something temporarily; to keep [[at bay]].
#: ''Let's try to '''hold off''' the lawyers until we are ready for them.''
#* '''November 2 2014''', Daniel Taylor, "[http://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/nov/02/manchester-city-manchester-united-premier-league-match-report Sergio Agüero strike wins derby for Manchester City against 10-man United]," ''guardian.co.uk''
#*: The breakthrough came after 63 minutes as United’s unorthodox defence desperately tried to '''hold off''' a spell of sustained pressure.
# {{lb|en|idiomatic|transitive|intransitive}} To delay commencing (an action until some specified time or event has passed).
#: '''''Hold off''' (on) the decision one more day so I can answer your question.''
#: '''''Hold off''' (on) baking until I get there.''

